comments.body:
> Can we also do something similar for the case, when the maximum trip count is known? Currently the value is hardcoded to be 16 iterations or higher, IIRC

@alexey-bataev Thank you for pointing out this issue.  Are you referring to `TinyTripCountVectorThreshold` = 16? If so, I think we could probably remove `CM_ScalarEpilogueNotAllowedLowTripLoop` directly.

However, when `CM_ScalarEpilogueNotAllowedLowTripLoop` is in effect, `computeMaxVF` will prioritize fixed VFs without a scalar epilogue, and `isOutsideLoopWorkProfitable` doesn’t seem to account for the scalar epilogue cost yet (not sure whether `MinTC = alignTo(MinTC, IntVF)` is good enough for that). So this might be worth handling in a separate patch I think.
